Russian Movers: Mechel, Raspadskaya, Rosneft Shares are Active

-- B y   J a s o n   C o r c o r a n
-- 
2011-03-16T16:32:20Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-16/russian-movers-mechel-raspadskaya-rosneft-shares-are-active.html
The 30-stock Micex Index rose 0.3
percent to 1,705.18 by the 6:45 p.m. close in Moscow. The
dollar-denominated RTS Index gained 0.5 percent to 1,915.95.  The following were among the most active stocks in the
Russian market today. Stock symbols are in parenthesis.  OAO  Raspadskaya (RASP)   gained by its most in three weeks
after three people with knowledge of the matter said yesterday
that OAO  Mechel (MTLR)  is considering acquiring shares in the Russian
coal producer. The stock surged 3.2 percent to 189.5 rubles, its
biggest gain since Feb. 21.  Mechel,  Russia ’s largest miner of steelmaking coal, climbed
for the third session in the past four, adding 2 percent to
842.6 rubles.  OAO Rosneft (ROSN RX), Russia’s largest oil producer, added
1 percent to 252.41 rubles. Crude for April delivery rose as
much as $1.56 to $98.70 in  New York  as escalating violence in
Bahrain stoked concern turmoil may spill into neighboring  Saudi
Arabia , threatening supplies from the world’s biggest crude
exporter.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jason Corcoran in Moscow at 
 jcorcoran13@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Gavin Serkin at 
 gserkin@bloomberg.net  